{% extends "base.jinja2" %}

{% block content %}
<div class="container_12">
  <div class="wrapper indent-bottom4">
    <div class="grid_6">
      <div class="bg-color1 maxheight">
        <div class="indents">
          <h3 class="icon-1 p1">Hello!</h3>
          Sunny Meadows Child Care’s goal is to provide a safe 
          and happy place for children to learn and grow 
          physically, emotionally, intellectually, and socially at 
          their own pace.<br><br>
          Our staff meet all applicable Michigan's State Regulations, and are
          trained in Blood borne Pathogen CPR, First Aide Infant, Child and Adult.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid_6 last-col">
      <div class="bg-color3 maxheight">
        <div class="indents">
          <h3 class="icon-2 p1">Mission Statement</h3>
          The mission of Sunny Meadows Child Care is to 
          provide quality childcare for all families.  This service is 
          given in a safe, healthy, and developmentally 
          appropriate environment where trained and loving 
          teachers provide educational opportunities for the well-rounded
          growth and development of each child.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="wrapper indent-bottom4">
    <div class="grid_4">
      <figure>
      <img src="static/img/page1-img1.jpg" alt="">
      </figure>
      <div class="bg-color2">
        <div class="indents1">
          <h3 class="p3">Program Philosophy</h3>
          <p class="p2">
                      We believe children learn through play and benefit 
            from a structured, yet flexible schedule.  Activities that 
            stimulate sensory motor development, language 
            development, and social interaction are offered and the 
            development of strong self-esteem is also a major goal.  
            Children will be taught to respect each other, adults, and 
            property.
          </p>
          <p class="p2">
                      We respect parents as the primary and most 
            important provider of care and nurturing, and believe 
            parents and teachers are partners in a child’s care and 
            education.
            </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <a href="about" class="button bg-color1">More about us</a>
    </div>
    <div class="grid_4">
      <h3 class="box-title bg-color4">Programs</h3>
      <ul class="list-1">
        <li>
        <a href="programs#infant_toddler_program" class="bg-color5">
          <div class="num">1</div>
          <strong><u>Infants & Toddlers</u><strong><br><br>
              By using defined practices of Toddler
              development, caregivers develop close, supportive 
              relationships with the children in their care and families.
            </a>
            </li>
            <li>
            <a href="programs#preshool_program" class="bg-color0">
              <div class="num">2</div>
              <strong><u>Preschoolers</u></strong><br><br>
              Children start learning numbers, the alphabet, 
              colors, shapes, eye-hand coordination, music melodies and
              more! We use activities to foster the growth and development. 
            </a>
            </li>
            <li>
            <a href="programs#before_after_program" class="bg-color1">
              <div class="num">3</div>
              <strong><u>Before & After School</u></strong><br><br>
              We provide indoor and outdoor activities, we offer arts 
              and crafts, reading time we also have game time (game 
              time is limited per day). School-age children can alsowork 
              on homework after school before parents pick them up.  )
            </a>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <a href="programs" class="button bg-color3">View our programs</a>
        </div>
